#: ../../M/Moores-Law.rst:5
msgid "Moore's Law"
msgstr "Moore's Law"

#: ../../M/Moores-Law.rst:7
msgid "/morz law/, prov\\."
msgstr "/morz law/, ことわざ"

#: ../../M/Moores-Law.rst:9
msgid ""
"Any one of several similar folk theorems that fit computing capacity or cost"
" to a 2t exponential curve, with doubling time close to a year. The most "
"common fits component density to such a curve (previous versions of this "
"entry gave that form). Another variant asserts that the dollar cost of "
"constant computing power decreases on the same curve. The original Moore's "
"Law, first uttered in 1965 by semiconductor engineer Gordon Moore (who co-"
"founded Intel four years later), spoke of the number of components on the "
"lowest-cost silicon integrated circuits — but Moore's own formulation varied"
" somewhat over the years, and reconstructing the meaning of the terminology "
"he used in the original turns out to be fraught with difficulties. Further "
"variants were spawned by Intel's PR department and various journalists."
msgstr ""
"計算能力やコストを倍増時間が一年に近い2tの指数曲線に当てはめる、いくつかの類似した俗説定理のいずれか。最も一般的なものは部品密度をそのような曲線に当てはめる(この項目の以前のバージョンはその形を挙げていた)。別の変種は、一定の計算能力のドル建てコストが同じ曲線上で減少すると主張する。元のMoore's"
" Lawは、1965年に半導体技術者Gordon "
"Moore(その四年後にIntelを共同設立した)によって初めて述べられ、最も低コストのシリコン集積回路上の部品数について語っていた。しかしMoore自身の定式化は年月とともにいくらか変化し、元のものでの彼の用語の意味を再構成することは困難に満ちていることが判明している。さらなる変種はIntelの広報部門とさまざまなジャーナリストによって生み出された。"

#: ../../M/Moores-Law.rst:15
msgid ""
"It has been `shown "
"<http://firstmonday.org/issues/issue7_11/tuomi/index.html>`_\\  that none of"
" the variants of Moore's Law actually fit the data very well (the price "
"curves within DRAM generations perhaps come closest). Nevertheless, Moore's "
"Law is constantly invoked to set up expectations about the next generation "
"of computing technology. See also :ref:`Parkinsons-Law-of-Data` and "
":ref:`Gatess-Law`\\."
msgstr ""
"Moore's Lawのどの変種も実際にはデータにあまりよく当てはまらないことが\\ `示されている "
"<http://firstmonday.org/issues/issue7_11/tuomi/index.html>`_\\ "
"(DRAM世代内の価格曲線がおそらく最も近い)。それでもなお、Moore's "
"Lawは次世代の計算技術についての期待を設定するために絶えず引き合いに出される。\\ :ref:`Parkinsons-Law-of-Data`\\ "
"と\\ :ref:`Gatess-Law`\\ も参照。"
